---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InvoiceDueDateCalculator from '../components/InvoiceDueDateCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Invoice Due Date Calculator — Payment Terms & Deadlines | Clockr"
	description="Calculate when your invoice is due from the invoice date and payment terms. Track days remaining, overdue status, and common UK payment terms like net 30."
	category="work"
>
	<div class="idc-page">
		<div class="idc-header">
			<div class="idc-eyebrow">
				<span class="idc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				Work & Business
			</div>
			<h1 class="idc-title">
				<span class="idc-gradient">Invoice Due Date Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="idc-subtitle">
				Calculate when your invoice is due and track payment deadlines
			</p>
		</div>

		<InvoiceDueDateCalculator client:load />

		<section class="idc-how">
			<h2 class="idc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="idc-how-card">
				<p>
					Payment terms define how long a customer has to pay after an invoice is
					issued. The due date is calculated by adding the agreed number of days
					to the invoice date — so an invoice dated 1 June with 30-day terms is
					due on 1 July. Enter your invoice date and select or enter the payment
					terms, and Clockr calculates the due date instantly and shows how many
					days remain until payment is expected.
				</p>
				<p>
					In UK business, common payment terms include 7 days (often for small
					jobs or cash-flow-sensitive work), 14 days, and 30 days. Net 30 — meaning
					payment within 30 calendar days of the invoice date — is the most widely
					used standard between businesses. Longer terms such as 60 or 90 days are
					sometimes negotiated for larger contracts or established supplier
					relationships, but they extend the wait before cash arrives.
				</p>
				<p>
					If an invoice is paid after the due date, UK law provides certain
					statutory rights under the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest)
					Act 1998, including the right to claim statutory interest and a fixed
					compensation sum on qualifying business-to-business debts. This
					calculator is for date arithmetic only — it does not constitute legal
					advice, and you should confirm your specific rights and procedures with
					a qualified adviser if payment is late.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="idc-faq">
			<h2 class="idc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="idc-faq-list">
				<details class="idc-faq-item">
					<summary class="idc-faq-question">How do I calculate an invoice due date?</summary>
					<div class="idc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Add the payment terms in days to the invoice date. For example, an
							invoice dated 15 March with 30-day terms is due on 14 April. Enter
							the invoice date in dd/mm/yyyy format, choose your payment terms (or
							enter a custom number of days), and the calculator shows the due
							date plus how many days remain or how overdue the invoice is.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="idc-faq-item">
					<summary class="idc-faq-question">What are standard payment terms in the UK?</summary>
					<div class="idc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The most common terms are 7, 14, and 30 days from the invoice date.
							Net 30 is the de facto standard for many B2B transactions — payment
							is expected within 30 calendar days. Smaller suppliers or freelancers
							may ask for 7 or 14 days; larger corporate buyers sometimes request
							60 or 90 days. Terms should always be agreed in writing before work
							begins or stated clearly on the invoice.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="idc-faq-item">
					<summary class="idc-faq-question">What does &ldquo;net 30&rdquo; mean on an invoice?</summary>
					<div class="idc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Net 30 means the full invoice amount is due within 30 calendar days
							of the invoice date — not 30 working days. An invoice dated 1
							January with net 30 terms is due on 31 January. &ldquo;Net&rdquo;
							indicates the full amount with no early-payment discount applied
							(unlike &ldquo;2/10 net 30&rdquo;, which offers a 2% discount if paid
							within 10 days).
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="idc-faq-item">
					<summary class="idc-faq-question">What happens if an invoice is paid late?</summary>
					<div class="idc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Once the due date passes without payment, the invoice is overdue.
							You may follow up with reminders, pause further work, or escalate
							through your agreed dispute process. For qualifying commercial
							debts in the UK, statutory interest and compensation may be
							claimable under the Late Payment of Commercial Debts legislation.
							Exact steps depend on your contract, relationship, and whether the
							debt meets the statutory criteria.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="idc-faq-item">
					<summary class="idc-faq-question">Can I charge interest on a late invoice?</summary>
					<div class="idc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							On qualifying business-to-business debts in the UK, you may be
							entitled to statutory simple interest at 8% above the Bank of England
							base rate, plus a fixed compensation amount, under the Late Payment
							of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998. Your contract may also specify
							its own late-payment interest clause. This is general factual
							information only — not legal advice. Consult a solicitor or debt
							recovery specialist for your specific situation.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="idc-faq-item">
					<summary class="idc-faq-question">How do I track multiple invoice due dates?</summary>
					<div class="idc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Run the calculator for each invoice separately, noting the due date
							and days remaining. For ongoing tracking, use a spreadsheet or
							accounting software with an aged debtors report — most list
							outstanding invoices by due date and flag overdue items. Pair this
							tool with the Business Days Calculator if you need working-day
							counts for follow-up schedules or internal SLAs.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="idc-related">
			<h3 class="idc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="idc-related-grid">
				<a href="/business-days" class="idc-related-card"
					><span class="idc-related-name">Business Days Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/project-deadline-calculator" class="idc-related-card"
					><span class="idc-related-name">Project Deadline Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/overtime-calculator" class="idc-related-card"
					><span class="idc-related-name">Overtime Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/work-hours-calculator" class="idc-related-card"
					><span class="idc-related-name">Work Hours Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.idc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.idc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.idc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.idc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-gradient {
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.idc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.idc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.idc-form-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.06);
	}

	.idc-inputs {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 28px;
	}

	.idc-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
	}

	.idc-label--block {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.idc-terms-section {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.12);
		padding-top: 24px;
	}

	.idc-terms-btns {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	.idc-terms-btn {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.idc-terms-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.6);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.08);
	}

	.idc-terms-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-to-rgb), 0.7);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.12);
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.1);
	}

	.idc-terms-btn-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.idc-terms-btn-sub {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		text-align: center;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	.idc-custom-terms {
		margin-top: 16px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.idc-custom-row {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	.idc-input {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		color-scheme: dark;
	}

	.idc-input--terms {
		max-width: 100px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.idc-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
	}

	.idc-custom-suffix {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	.idc-results {
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.idc-due-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.25);
		border-radius: 16px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		text-align: center;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.08);
	}

	.idc-due-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin-bottom: 8px;
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
	}

	.idc-due-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.2;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-days {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-days--overdue {
		color: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.95);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.idc-status {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
		padding: 8px 16px;
		border-radius: 999px;
	}

	.idc-status--on-time {
		background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.12);
		border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.35);
		color: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.95);
	}

	.idc-status--due-soon {
		background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.12);
		border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.35);
		color: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.95);
	}

	.idc-status--overdue {
		background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.12);
		border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.35);
		color: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.95);
	}

	.idc-quick {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.idc-quick-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-quick-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.idc-quick-btn {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.idc-quick-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.5);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.06);
	}

	.idc-quick-btn-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.idc-quick-btn-sub {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
	}

	.idc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.idc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.idc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.idc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.idc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.idc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.idc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.idc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.idc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.idc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.idc-faq-item[open] .idc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.idc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.idc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.idc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.idc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.idc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.idc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.idc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.4);
	}

	.idc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.idc-title {
			font-size: 40px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.idc-terms-btns {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}

		.idc-due-date {
			font-size: 24px;
		}

		.idc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
